summary: crowley kissing aziraphale, marking his neck with hickies and the angel clearing his throat and asking if crowley could, well,...
body:
crowley kissing aziraphale, marking his neck with hickies and the angel clearing his throat and asking if crowley could, well, if you wouldn’t mind, dear … place one Above the Collar … and crowley’s pupils go from | to O in a matter of seconds. can’t help it when your prim and proper, normally fussy husband asks you to mark him in a spot that’d be seen.

later, they’re at a park bench and crowley’s sitting at aziraphale’s side, lifts his hand to thumb at the mark on the angel’s neck … “should’ve given you another one,” he mutters, pauses to think for a moment. and then, drawling his words with this next bit, “… could do it now, of course.” and aziraphale has to swat his hand away and tell him to be civil – but it’s said with the tone of a man who is both exasperated and completely in love.

summary:
I've read about this Soulmate AU where you can hear when your Soulmate's listening to a song and:
IMAGINE CROWLEY AND...
body:
I’ve read about this Soulmate AU where you can hear when your Soulmate’s listening to a song and:

IMAGINE CROWLEY AND AZIRAPHALE

Aziraphale: Oh, no. No, no, no. No! Not again!

Gabriel: What?

Aziraphale: …He’s listening to Queen again…

OR

Crowley: Classic?! Are you shitt- Classic?! Come on, there’s better music out there! Anything but Classic, please!

AND WHAT IF THEY KNOW WHO’S THEIR SOULMATE

CAN YOU IMAGINE CROWLEY RUSHING OVER TO AZIRAPHALE:

Crowley: I’m begging you, stop it! Stop it or I’ll burn your bloody player!

Azirphale: Well, who plays the same songs of the same band over and over again, hm?!

AND THEN IT TURNS INTO A WAR BECAUSE THEY BOTH BELIEVE THAT THEIR MUSIC IS BETTER AND THEY WON’T STOP SO THEY’RE LIKE: MY MUSIC IS BETTER, I CAN PLAY IT LOUDER!

AND ONE DAY CROWLEY COMES BACK TO AZIRAPHALE WITH THE HEADACHE OF HIS LIFE

Crowley: Angel!

Aziraphale: My dear!

Both: …

Both: This has to stop!

Crowley: *breaking down* It’s exhausting, please, we NEED to stop

Aziraphale: *also breaking down* I know, I can’t do this anymore!
